tion%20you%20raised%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20ministry%20wrote%20on%20Monday.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIts%20response%20has%20ignited%20conversation%20about%20the%20validity%20of%20the%20folk%20belief%2C%20with%20more%20than%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fs.weibo.com%2Fweibo%3Fq%3D%2523%25E6%25B0%2591%25E6%2594%25BF%25E9%2583%25A8%25E5%259B%259E%25E5%25A4%258D%25E9%25BE%2599%25E5%25B9%25B4%25E4%25B8%258D%25E5%25AE%259C%25E7%25BB%2593%25E5%25A9%259A%2523%26Refer%3Dweibo_weibo%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E300%20million%20views%20on%20the%20topic%20on%20Weibo%2C%3C%2Fa%3E%20China's%20version%20of%20X.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20belief%20involves%20the%20lack%20of%20a%20%26quot%3Bbeginning%20of%20spring%26quot%3B%20day%2C%20also%20known%20as%20lichun%2C%20at%20the%20start%20of%20a%20lunar%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20year's%20lichun%20falls%20on%20February%204%2C%20before%20the%20Chinese%20Lunar%20New%20Year%20begins%20on%20February%2010%2C%20meaning%20the%20coming%20year%20won't%20include%20a%20beginning%20of%20spring%20day.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESuch%20a%20lunar%20year%20is%20sometimes%20dubbed%20the%20%26quot%3BYear%20of%20the%20Widow%26quot%3B%20because%20ancient%20superstition%20associates%20spring%20with%20masculine%20energy%2C%20and%20getting%20married%20at%20such%20a%20time%20is%20thought%20to%20bring%20bad%20luck%20and%20divorce.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhich%20year%20doesn't%20have%20widows%3F%20What%20does%20spring%20have%20anything%20to%20do%20with%20it%3F%26quot%3B%20Beijing-based%20blogger%20Crying%2C%20Giggling%2C%20Laughing%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fweibo.com%2F6467575955%3Frefer_flag%3D1001030103_%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ewrote%20on%20Weibo.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere%20surely%20must%20be%20a%20reason%20behind%20thousands%20of%20years%20of%20folk%20tradition%2C%26quot%3B%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fweibo.com%2F5993531560%2FNDlxp52QO%3Frefer_flag%3D1001030103_%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eanother%20person%2