e%20I%20last%20left%20the%20country.%20I%20studied%20abroad%20in%20South%20Korea%20in%202012.%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3EI%20eagerly%20accepted%20my%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fchina-work-culture-love-hate-relationship-tech-worker-relocation-2023-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efirst%20job%20in%20China%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3ESoon%20after%20arriving%2C%20I%20adjusted%20to%20living%20and%20working%20in%20China.%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI%20taught%20at%20an%20English%20training%20center%20in%20Yantai%2C%20from%202019%20to%202021.%20My%20salary%20was%20between%2010%2C000-13%2C000%20RMB%20a%20month%2C%20or%20about%20%241%2C400-%241%2C820.%20The%20job%20package%20included%20an%20apartment%2C%20so%20I%20only%20had%20to%20cover%20quarterly%20maintenance%20fees%20and%20expenses.%20My%20other%20expenses%20%E2%80%94%20including%20groceries%2C%20water%20for%20my%20dispenser%2C%20weekly%20online%20therapy%2C%20and%20stickers%20for%20my%20younger%20students%20%E2%80%94%20worked%20out%20to%20less%20than%20%24600%20a%20month.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223264%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22People%20by%20the%20water%20at%20Yangma%20Island%20in%20Yantai%2C%20China%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65b0c954617029e90a5fd202%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222448%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EAuthor%20visiting%20Yangma%20Island%20in%20Yantai%20in%202019.%3Cp%3EDanielle%20Marcano%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EYantai%20is%20a%20coastal%20city%20in%20northern%20China%2C%20around%20440%20miles%20southeast%20of%20Beijing.%20I%20met%20a%20lot%20of%20curious%20students%20who%20would%20ask%20me%20questions%20about%20America.%20The%20most%20common%20question%20I%20heard%20was%2C%20%26quot%3BDo%20you%20know%20the%20Lakers%3F%26quot%3B%20When%20I%20wasn't%20working%2C%20I%20could%20do%20things%20like%20explore%20Yangma%20Island%2C%20sample%20wine%20at%20the%20famous%20Changyu%20winery%2C%20and%20pick%20fresh%20berries%20from%20a%20local%20farm.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EI%20had%20to%20find%20a%20new%20purpose%20during%20the%20pandemic.%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20January%202020%2C%20I%20went%20to%20Los%20Angeles%20to%20visit%20my%20family%20for%20Chinese%20New%20Year.%20My%20dad%20and%20I%20were%20having%20breakfast%20when%20a%20news%20report%20on%20TV%20said%20that%20the%20US%20had%20its%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcoronavirus-pandemic-timeline-history-major-events-2020-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efirst%20confirmed%20case%20of%20COVID-19%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Later%20that%20day%2C%20I%20received%20a%20message%20from%20my%20director%2C%20saying%20that%20there%20was%20a%20chance%20that%20China%20would%20close%20its%20borders%20and%20I%20needed%20to%20fly%20back%20as%20soon%20as%20possible.%20A%20few%20days%20later%2C%20I%20returned%20to%20China.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20I%20came%20back%2C%20it%20felt%20like%20a%20ghost%20town.%20There%20were%20barely%20any%20cars%20or%20people.%20The%20only%20thing%20I%20could%20hear%20was%20the%20wind%20blowing%20past%20my%20ears.%20Our%20training%20center%20decided%20to%20start%20teaching%20students%20from%20home.%20It%20was%20clear%20that%20I%20needed%20another%20career%20shift.%20However%2C%20I%20had%20no%20interest%20in%20returning%20to%20the%20US.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EI%20was%20determined%20to%20stop%20teaching%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20most%20of%20my%20WeChat%20conversations%2C%20headhunters%20would%20ask%20why%20I%20wanted%20to%20quit%20teaching%20and%20often%20try%20to%20persuade%20me%20by%20mentioning%20higher%20salary%20options.%20But%20as%20much%20as%20I%20enjoyed%20working%20with%20my%20students%2C%20I%20knew%20my%20true%20calling%20was%20beyond%20the%20classroom.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESince%202021%2C%20I've%20worked%20as%20a%20tech%20copywriter%20in%20Shenzhen%2C%20a%20Chinese%20city%20about%20a%2015-minute%20train%20ride%20from%20Hong%20Kong.%20While%20I%20can't%20disclose%20exactly%20how%20much%20I%20earn%20as%20a%20copywriter%2C%20the%20average%20salary%20I've%20seen%20in%20other%20copywriting%20positions%20ranges%20between%2018%2C000%20to%2020%2C000%20RMB%20a%20month%2C%20or%20%242%2C540%20to%20%243%2C777%2C%20based%20on%20experience%20%E2%80%94%20close%20to%20double%20what%20I%20was%20making%20teaching.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222304%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Woman%20high%20fiving%20Mickey%20Mouse%20at%20Disneyland%20Hong%20KOng%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65b1ce6e43bb77284ba071aa%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221728%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EAuthor%20at%20Hong%20Kong%20Disneyland%3Cp%3EDanielle%20Marcano%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EI%20pay%20between%205%2C000-6%2C000%20RMB%20for%20a%20one-bedroom%20apartment%20and%20utilities.%20I%20haven't%20had%20any%20roommates%20during%20my%20time%20in%20China%2C%20and%20while%20living%20on%20my%20own%20is%20more%20expensive%2C%20I%20value%20a%20quiet%20space%20to%20watch%20movies%20and%20play%20video%20games.%20My%20favorite%20part%20of%20the%20apartment%20I'm%20in%20now%20is%20the%20night-time%20view%20from%20the%20balcony%2C%20where%20multiple%20colors%20and%20moving%20projections%20are%20always%20on%20display.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EMy%20dating%20life%20is%20difficult%2C%20but%20I%20plan%20to%20stay%20in%20China.%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI've%20found%20loneliness%20the%20most%20challenging%20part%20of%20being%20an%20expat%20in%20China.%20I%20still%20attend%20therapy%2C%20and%20while%20the%20price%20has%20increased%20over%20time%2C%20it%20has%20been%20essential%20to%20my%20mental%20health.%20Despite%20thousands%20of%20expats%20living%20in%20Shenzhen%20%E2%80%94%20and%20more%20in%20nearby%20Hong%20Kong%20%E2%80%94%20I%20spend%20most%20of%20my%20time%20alone.%20The%20majority%20of%20my%20close%20friends%20are%20either%20in%20a%20relationship%20or%20married.%20Meanwhile%2C%20I'm%2030%20and%20single.%20Despite%20my%20accomplishments%20in%20China%2C%20I'm%20still%20asked%20by%20some%20family%20members%20why%20I'm%20not%20married.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20my%20experience%2C%20dating%20in%20China%20is%20complicated.%20I'm%20not%20opposed%20to%20dating%20Chinese%20men%2C%20but%20I%20often%20worry%20about%20the%20language%20barrier%20and%20cultural%20differences.%20My%20Chinese%20skills%20are%20limited%20to%20a%20few%20phrases.%20Conversely%2C%20single%20expat%20men%20have%20expressed%20interest%20in%20me%2C%20but%20they'll%20also%20tell%20me%20they're%20not%20looking%20for%20anything%20serious.%20In%20other%20words%2C%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsituationship-dating-trend-young-singles-relationship-status-gen-z-2023-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esituationship%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20say%2C%20%26quot%3BNo%20way.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20me%2C%202023%20was%20a%20rough%20year%20full%20of%20heartbreak%2C%20self-doubt%2C%20and%20stress-related%20health%20issues.%20Despite%20my%20fears%2C%20I'm%20confident%20that%20the%20support%20system%20I%20built%20here%20%E2%80%94%20my%20therapist%2C%20friends%2C%20and%20life%20coaches%20%E2%80%94%20will%20help%20me%20build%20the%20confidence%20I%20need%20to%20return%20to%20the%20dating%20scene.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUltimately%2C%20it's%20about%20being%20open%20to%20people%20and%20their%20perspectives.%20It's%20a%20similar%20mindset%20I%20had%20when%20I%20found%20the%20opportunity%20to%20work%20in%20China%20in%20the%20first%20place.%20Expect%20the%20unexpected.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EGot%20a%20personal%20essay%20about%20living%20abroad%2C%20parenting%2C%20or%20a%20midlife%20crisis%20that%20you%20want%20to%20share%3F%20Get%20in%20touch%20with%20the%20editor%3A%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%20nofollow%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22mailto%3Aakarplus%40insider.com%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cu%3Eakarplus%40insider.com%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20